
This directory contains host-side and firmware-adjacent tests for the keyswitch
tester firmware.

Current test suites:

- `test_protocol/` for command parsing
- `test_domain/` for homing and motion state logic
- `test_integration/` for command-to-domain interaction tests

Run all host tests with:

```powershell
Set-Location "c:\git\BTT SKR2 Testing"
& ".\test\run_host_tests.ps1"
```

Export a local simulated probe-workflow curve with:

```powershell
Set-Location "c:\git\BTT SKR2 Testing"
& ".\test\run_simulated_probe_workflow.ps1"
```

That reruns the host suite, then writes `tools\arm-dashboard\simulated-probe-curve.json` from the host-side probe workflow simulator so the dashboard can visualize the response curve without board hardware.

These tests intentionally target the extracted `lib/keyswitch_core/` layer so
the critical behavior can be validated without requiring the SKR2 hardware.

Run live-board serial integration tests with:

```powershell
Set-Location "c:\git\BTT SKR2 Testing"
& ".\test\run_live_serial_tests.ps1"
```

Add `-IncludeMotion` when it is safe to execute `home` and `backoff` against the attached hardware.

Run the dedicated load-cell probe-cycle bring-up path with:

```powershell
Set-Location "c:\git\BTT SKR2 Testing"
& ".\test\run_probe_cycle.ps1" -AllowUnverifiedMotion -LoadCellConnector SKR2_DET -LoadCellSource HX711 -LoadCellThreshold 1000 -PressTargetSteps 40 -CycleCount 5
```

That script configures the load-cell path, runs `HOME`, applies `PRESSPOS`, executes `CYCLE`, and leaves the driver disabled on shutdown. Today it validates the operator path and motion routine; real HX711/ADC stop behavior still depends on the future acquisition implementation in `src/load_cell.cpp`.
